commit.message: docs: mention Black and flake8 in the Contribution guide

build: make the flake8 config global

This way, there is no need for copying its configuration
to different places / tools setup anymore.
style: fix the various, mostly formatting issues reported by flake8

ci: more practical settings of the flake8 rules

* W605 "Invalid escape sequence" might become
  a syntax error in the future - check it now already
* ignore various common indentation problems
* ignore long lines (E501)

fix(mathjax-renderer): inline math handling (#195)

Previously the renderer was converting mathjax unsupported inline math delimiters $ to
block math delimiters $$ which are not equivalent.

Now it instead converts inline math delim $ to the mathjax supported inline
math delim \( \) which have the expected equivalent behavior (i.e. showing the math in-line).

---------

Co-authored-by: Petr Bodnar <p.bodnar@centrum.cz>

commit.message: feat(html-renderer): option to skip HTML tokens parsing (#74)

feat: allow just 1 dash in Table delimiter cells (#131)

In or around [#371](github/markup#371), GFM relaxed constraints on the minimal number of required dashes in table delimiter row.

So we relax the constraints as well. To "compensate" for this change,
we check the format of the delimiter row more thoroughly (although
we still do *not* check number of cells in the delimiter row).

fix: make local installation work again with pip 23.2 and above

Surprise, Python doesn't support `-SNAPSHOT` versions like Maven
does! Moreover, pip version 23.2 removed support for versions
which don't conform to PEP 440.

So we make the snapshot version conformant by using the `.dev`
suffix (equivalent to `.dev0`) which basically serves the same
purpose as `-SNAPSHOT`. By this, we make this snippet from the
README work again:

```sh
git clone https://github.com/miyuchina/mistletoe.git
cd mistletoe
pip3 install -e .
```

feat(markdown-renderer): option to normalize whitespace (#202)

This follows #197 and adds the possibility to switch ON the
original renderer behavior when the space after list marker (called
leader in mistletoe) collapsed just to 1 space.

The same option can also be used to control other types of
"whitespace normalization" in the future.

commit.message:
feat: keep the original content spacing after the list marker (#196)

A list item such as ` -   list item` consists of margin indentation
 (A), a list marker (B), 1-4 spaces (C) and contents.
The old code recorded the width from A to C as `ListItem.prepend` and
 B as `ListItem.leader`,
but the Markdown renderer always skipped margin indentation and output
exactly just 1 space after every list marker, such as `- list item`.

After this change, the width of A is recorded as `ListItem.indentation`,
so that the Markdown renderer can correctly restore both A and C.
But the formatting features of other tokens skip margin indentation (A),
for consistency of all formatting features,
the Markdown renderer only restores C, such as `-   list item`.
fix: penultimate lines of multiline fragments being ignored by the Markdown renderer (#201)

commit.message: chore: next version is 1.3.0
chore: version 1.2.1

fix: make `mistletoe.HTMLRenderer` work again

Backwards compatibility was actually broken in #182 inadvertently -
it didn't cover the case when the old `HTMLRenderer` was imported directly
from the `mistletoe` package.

Note: The `# noqa: F401` comment is for the flake8 linter, it suppresses
the `imported but unused` rule.
chore: next version is 1.2.1
chore: next dev version
chore: version 1.2.0

refactor: use strict PascalCase for class names (#182)

This makes it more practical when compound class
names are introduced.

For backwards compatibility, we also introduce aliases
for the old names, marking them as deprecated.

test: unify assertEqual calls in all the tests (#185)

This one was also omitted by mistake in 86f3a2f.

fix: escape special characters in URLs (#190)

If `\url{}` is used within LaTeX macros like `\multicolumn` and if the
link to be rendered contains `#` or `%` as typical confluence links like
https://site.com/confluence/display/TEST/TEST-042%3A+Foo#target are
bound to, pdflatex (from TeX Live 2019) fails with errors. This patch
fixes that by escaping these two characters.

NB: if `\url{}` with such links is used outside of multicolumn-macros,
they work regardless of whether these characters are escaped, and the
result remains the same.

Additionally, make the LaTeX renderer %-quote unsafe chars in urls like
other renderers do (e.g.,  in Jira and XWiki renderers).

Resolves #114.
Added an option to the Table class to interrupt paragraphs or not during parsing.

Made tables interrupt paragraphs (#166).

This is done by overriding the `check_interrupts_paragraph` method on the `Table` class.
Changed to use more generic mechanism to check for end of block quotes and list items.
Moved the logic for checking if a block token interrupts a paragraph from Paragraph.read() to the respective block token classes.
